- "2022-2023 season" is the specific season year being queried.

- "Seasoned mentors" refers to coaches with more than 5 years of coaching experience;
- "Battles" refers to games played in the season;
- "Vast arena" is a metaphor for the competitive environment of the NHL.

- The win percentage is calculated as the total number of wins divided by the total number of games played.;
- Teams are ranked within their leagues based on their total wins and, in case of a tie, the total number of games played.;
- The query uses a dense rank to avoid gaps in the ranking if multiple teams have the same number of wins and games played.

sql:
SELECT 
    ROUND(CAST(SUM(s.goals) AS REAL) / COUNT(DISTINCT s.player_id), 2) AS average_goals
FROM stats s;

